The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, July 11, 2004 				Metro Recommends

	THE VCD 
	(MusicWorld, Rs 299) In the uncertain climes of the Russian revolution begins the torrid love affair of doctor-poet Zhivago. Director David Lean builds up an epic romance through flashbacks and adoring close-ups, with Omar Sharif and Julie Christie in the lead. This screen adaptation of the Boris Pasternak novel was nominated for 10 Oscars. It won five. THE EVENT				 																																	(Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm-7.30 pm) The photo exhibition by Sandesh Bhandare explores tamasha, a major folk art form of rural India. Bhandares probing lens captures some images of this performing art which was once a popular source of entertainment for the Mughal and Peshwa armies. THE SHOW				 																																	(Sunday, 12.30 pm, ETV Bangla) Saunter through the streets of London and savour the sights with radio personalities Sravonti and Ameen Sayani. The economy travel show takes you around the Bards home at Stratford-upon-Avon, the imposing Buckingham Palace or the county of Kent where Rahul Dravid played cricket. 

